                <h2>Family and origins</h2>
                <p>Harris was born on April 9, 1967 in Los Angeles. He is the son of actor Berkeley Harris, who appeared mainly in Western films, and TV producer Susan Harris (née Spivak), who created The Golden Girls among other series. His father, born in North Carolina, came from a Quaker background, and his mother is Jewish but not religious. He was raised by his mother following his parents' divorce when he was aged two. Harris has stated that his upbringing was entirely secular and that his parents rarely discussed religion, though he also stated that he was not raised as an atheist.</p>
